  85,1,""
  85,2,""
  85,3,""
  85,4,""
  85,5,"(a) Advice, howsoever reasonable and well-supported by arguments, can be effective only when the hearer is serious about it. If the hearer is not serious, the advice will not reach his heart. Such arguments as deeply move a serious-minded person, will only cause a frivolous person to engage in meaningless discussions."
  85,6,""
  85,7,""
